  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Bilateral Gluteal Fascio-myo-cutaneous Advancement Flap is a modified technique used in
      Treatment of Recurrent Sacrococcygeal Pilonidal sinus
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with recurrent pilonidal sinus disease are recruited to undergo Bilateral Gluteal
      Fascio-myo-cutaneous Advancement Flap technique under spinal anesthesia in order to prevent
      recurrence.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
